content.description: Starts sitting with hands in the 'pots' right of center of the wall. Climb to the knobs and traverse them right. Exit at the arete.
content.location: At the 'You Are What You Is' boulders located directly across from the finish to the 'Enclave Problem', just upstream from the Spearpoint boulder. There is a moss covered tree trunk that sits between the two boulders.

content.description: Climb the pockets up the right side of the You Are What You Is boulder.
content.location: At the 'You Are What You Is' boulders located directly across from the finish to the 'Enclave Problem', just upstream from the Spearpoint boulder. There is a moss covered tree trunk that sits between the two boulders.

content.description: SDS on the low horizontal rail around the left side of Spearpoint - finishes by moving up the slight prow towards the jug pocket.
content.location: Located around the left of Spearpoint Arete on the backside of the boulder. SDS on the horizontal rail

content.description: Traverse is done left to right. For a V6, start on the far left of the dappled wall with your left foot on the ledge and hands matched. Move right through crimpers and scarce feet to a right-angling ledge (V4 starts here). Traverse right to a flake (V2 starts here). Follow the offset ledge system, drop into horizontal finger crack and finish by traversing the crack.
content.location: On the dappled south wall just behind the 'You Are What You Is' boulders.

content.description: Starts sitting at bulge left of Spearpoint with your left hand underclinging the belly of the boulder and your right hand on the sloper side rail. Climb to the arete and finish as with Spearpoint Arete.
Start sitting on the right side of the boulder with hands matched on the lowest slopers. Climb the arete but eliminate left hand holds, confining the left hand to the arete.
content.location: At the entrance to the Enclave

content.description:
Start sitting at the far left margin of the Buzzcut wall. Traverse low under the low roof via the shelf system. Exit where the roof ends. 

  Note: A boulder has washed up against the start of the problem, blocking the first couple moves.
content.location: Just upstream from the Diving Board and The Dissertion Cave, on the wall to the left of the Buzzcut Boulder which sits under a distinctive roof.

content.description: Sit down at the right side of the boulder below the overhanging arete with hands matched on lowest slopers. Climb the arete.
content.location: At the entrance to the Enclave

content.description: Not sure on FA or if has another name. If someone knows of either, I'd be happy to correct the info. Great during the winter, probably too chossy in the spring/summer.Very easy problem, great warm up. SDS matching on the obvious jug. Move up to left on good ledges and mantle the top.Variations exist with lower holds and more awkward sit starts, possibly a grade harder.
content.location: The small boulder this problem is on is directly below and to the left of Spearpoint, as pictured.

content.description: A fun little problem that starts on an edge and ends with a topout. you can either hike back down or jump onto a crash pad below. (I did the latter)
content.location: Just downstream from "The Diving Board" on the opposite bank.

content.description: Easy and fun. Not sure if this is one of the other variations for Afraid of Spearpoint. Or if this specific variation has another name… This one is a fun little problem. Located just to the left of Spearpoint Arete. Same Boulder as Afraid of Spearpoint. Right hand on the rock jutting out that begins Afraid of Spearpoint. Left hand start on the large jutting out piece of rock directly to the left. Match both hands and proceed left then top out.
content.location: Located just to the left of spearpoint arete. SameBoulder as Afraid of Spearpoint.

content.description: Start underclinging on a flake and follow the crack. Match on some shitty coral-like rock before the mini roof.
content.location: Located on the tres bien traverse wall towards the left side.

content.description: Starts with hands on flat ledge feet pushed into roof then you slap out right to a rounded jug which you then match. After matching left heel hook just below matching point and then throw right again to ledge continue up the ledge until you get tho the moss at this point you mantle up and top out the boulder.
content.location: Face the Spearpoint boulder then turn directly around and you will see a wall across the dried creek. Follow the wall to the left for about 30 ft passing carlitos adventure on the right.

content.description: Start with both hands on the ledge and jump for the end of the board. Mantel.
content.location: Upstream from The Tres Bien Wall on the same side of the run-off. Rock feature jutting out from the wall is shaped like a diving board.

content.description: Start on two edges and work along the roof until you pull yourself over the edge and finish by matching on a small crimp.
content.location: Directly across from the Spearhead Boulder inside a cave.

content.description: Easy approach. Lots of cool problems close together with decent landings. Fun traverses and little overhang/cave routes.
